# AlignAI Website Standards

## Canonical Brief Context (Mar 2026)

- Source of truth: `AlignAI_Website_Complete_Brief_Mar2026_1.docx`
- Build decisions must follow brief mockups and acceptance criteria when conflicts appear.
- Brand architecture is dual: **ByteStream Strategies Inc.** (company) + **AlignAI** (framework/product).

## Architecture

- Next.js App Router with static export (`output: "export"`)
- TypeScript strict mode
- Server Components by default; `"use client"` only for interactive elements
- Serverless chat function lives in `netlify/functions/`, not in `app/api/`
- Blog content sourced from `data/posts.json`; no CMS
- Milestone model: M1 visual stubs, M3 live chatbot, M4 live auth/client area

## Design Tokens

Colors (use Tailwind classes, never raw hex):
- `navy` #0C1E39, `deep-blue` #274185, `mid-blue` #407BB7
- `cyan` #63BCE7, `slate` #84899A, `light-slate` #C8CDD8, `off-white` #F4F6F9
- `white` #FFFFFF only for cards/text on dark sections (not full-width section fills)

Typography:
- Headings: `font-heading` (Sora) — H1 700 with `-0.03em` tracking, H2/H3 600
- Body: `font-body` (Inter) 16–17px, `leading-body` 1.65, max-w-prose 680px
- Nav links: Inter 600, 13px, ALL CAPS, letter-spacing `0.07em`
- Buttons: Inter 600, 14px

Buttons: `bg-mid-blue text-white rounded-btn` (4px radius), flat fill only, **no outline variant as default CTA**

## Strict Rules

- **NO gradients** — solid backgrounds only
- Container max-width 1200px (`container-main` class)
- Section backgrounds alternate: navy → off-white → white → off-white
- 1px mid-blue divider (`section-divider` class) between major sections
- CTA strip appears on all pages except `/contact`
- No drop shadows/glassmorphism/neumorphism/parallax/particle effects
- No sidebars; single-column narrative flow on content pages
- Breakpoints must validate at 390px, 768px, 1440px
- Header/footer brand text should use **ByteStream Strategies** hierarchy, with AlignAI as framework emphasis
- Contact canonical email: `bburke@bytestream.ca`
- Footer copyright canonical text: `© 2026 ByteStream Strategies Inc.`

## Accessibility

- WCAG 2.1 AA minimum
- All interactive elements keyboard accessible
- Visible focus outlines (cyan)
- Contrast ratio ≥4.5:1
- Semantic HTML, ARIA labels on non-obvious controls
- Skip-to-content link in root layout

## Performance

- Static export — no server runtime
- Fonts loaded via `next/font` with `display: swap`
- Images unoptimized (static export) but use WebP when possible
- No render-blocking client JS; minimize `"use client"` boundaries
- Target Lighthouse performance >= 90 all pages
- Explicit width/height on images; lazy-load non-critical images

## SEO

- Every page exports Metadata with title + description + OG tags
- JSON-LD Organization schema in root layout
- Static sitemap.xml and robots.txt in `/public`

## Chatbot & Security

- Widget visible globally; visual stub in M1, live API in M3
- Chat API via serverless proxy only; Anthropic key in environment variables only
- Session-scoped conversation history only (no cross-session persistence)
- Basic rate limiting is mandatory
- Never expose API keys in client bundles, public files, or repository history
